The paper deals with algorithms for the computation of BWT and LCP arrays, which are commonly used in bioinformatics and string processing. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an external memory algorithm, which involves efficient use of disk I/O, indicating that it could also belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the computation of maximal repeats, which is a problem in combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of scan-based algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the experimental results show that the proposed algorithm outperforms existing algorithms, which could indicate that the paper belongs to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
